1. No commercial sale or commercial distribution
-------------------------------------------------
You may NOT sell CatKey, charge a fee for CatKey, bundle CatKey with a
paid product or service, or otherwise distribute CatKey (in source or
binary form, original or modified) primarily for commercial advantage
or monetary compensation. CatKey is free software for the community.


2. No obfuscated or packed redistribution
------------------------------------------
You may NOT distribute CatKey, or any build/derivative of CatKey, in a
form that is obfuscated, packed, encrypted, or otherwise made
deliberately difficult to inspect. Any distributed build must:

  a. correspond exactly to publicly available, unmodified-or-clearly-
     marked source code; and
  b. remain reasonably auditable (no packers, crypters, protectors, or
     anti-analysis measures).

This exists so users can always verify that a CatKey build has not been
tampered with.


3. Independent verification required before distribution
--------------------------------------------------------
Before you build CatKey and distribute that build to others, the build
MUST be verifiable and independently verified:

  a. Publish the exact source used for the build.
  b. Make the build reproducible (document the toolchain and steps; see
     build.ps1 / build.sh and docs/).
  c. Publish checksums (e.g. SHA-256) of every distributed artifact.
  d. Have at least one independent party reproduce the build from the
     published source and confirm the checksums match before the build
     is offered for download.

Do not distribute unsigned or unverified binaries as if they were
official. See docs/ (README) for the rationale.


4. Attribution and ShareAlike
------------------------------
As required by CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, you must give appropriate credit, link
to this license, indicate any changes, and license your modifications
under the same terms (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).


5. Warranty disclaimer
----------------------
CatKey is provided "AS IS", without warranty of any kind. See Section 5
of "CC-BY-NC-SA LICENSE" for the full disclaimer of warranties and
limitation of liability.


Third-party components (e.g. PySide6/Qt, pynput) remain under their own
respective licenses.
